the reference to `&EmbedFileSystem` should be `&render.EmbedFileSystem`

This will make more sense to people using the library in their own package i.e. not called "render").

Render templates from an embedded filesystem provides as an `embed.FS`.

### Description

- Introduced in the stdlib with go version 1.16, the package embed provides access to files embedded in the running Go program
- As embed is now the standard approach to embed files, `render` should be able to use templates from `embed.FS` out of the box.

### Proposed changes

- Add `EmbedFileSystem` which implements `render.FileSystem` and acts as an adapter to `embed.FS`
- Requires upgrade of go version to `1.16`
- Avoids breaking changes in the API of the `render`

### Example usage

```golang
// ...

//go:embed templates/*.html templates/*.tmpl
var embeddedTemplates embed.FS

// ...

r := render.New(render.Options{
    Directory: "templates",
    FileSystem: &EmbedFileSystem{
        FS: embeddedTemplates,
    },
    Extensions: []string{".html", ".tmpl"},
})
// ...
```

### References

- Package embed: https://golang.org/pkg/embed/

